bib_record.title: STRUCTURE OF 19-O FROM MEASUREMENT AND R-MATRIX ANALYSIS OF SIGMA(THETA) FOR 18-O(N,N)18-O AND 18-O(N,N') 18-O (1.98 MEV)

free_txt: FINITE GEOMETRY AND MULTIPLE SCATTERING USING MONTE
CARLO TECHNIQUES
5.0 CM THICK AND 11.25 CM IN DIAMETER
TOTAL UNCERTAINTY OF 6 PERCENT FOR ELASTIC SCATTERING
AND 8 PERCENT FOR INELASTIC SCATTERING CROSS SECTION.
COMPONENTS OF TOTAL UNCERTAINTY ARE LISTED BELOW:
1 PERCENT DUE TO UNCERTAINTY IN DISTANCES BETWEEN THE
DETECTOR, SAMPLE AND SOURCE, 1 PERCENT DUE TO THE
UNCERTAINTY IN NUCLEI NUMBER, 1 PERCENT DUE TO THE
COUNTING STATISTICS IN THE DETECTOR PEAK SUM FOR THE
ELASTIC SCATTERING AND LESS THAN 3 PERCENT FOR THE
INELASTIC SCATTERING. 1 PERCENT DUE TO THE COUNTING
STATISTICS IN THE MONITOR PEAK SUM. UNCERTAINTY IN THE
RELATIVE EFFICIENCY WAS LESS THAN 2 PERCENT, INCLUDING
CHARGE NORMALIZATION ERROR AND GAS TARGET PRESSURE
VARIATION. UNCERTAINTY IN ZERO DEGREE YIELD IS LESS
THAN 1 PERCENT. UNCERTAINTY IN MULTIPLE SCATTERING AND
FINITE GEOMETRY CORRECTION IS ABOUT 3 PERCENT FOR THE
ELASTIC SCATTERING AND 5 PERCENT FOR THE INELASTIC.
TRITIUM GAS CELL
39.3 GRAMS ULTRAPURE WATER, WITH OXYGEN ISOTOPICALLY
ENRICHED TO 98.2 PERCENT, IN RIGHT-CIRCULAR CYLINDRICAL
STAINLESS-STEEL CAN, 3.65CM IN DIAMETER AND HEIGHT
DATA TAKEN FROM THESIS.
